- `n`: This represents the current position of the cursor in the file, usually in terms of the number of characters from the beginning of the file.
- `64k`: This represents the total size of the file in kilobytes (KB).

For example, if you see "123/64k", it means that the cursor is currently at the 123rd character in a file that is 64 kilobytes in size.

This kind of indicator is useful for quickly understanding your position within a file and the overall size of the file you are working on.
